listitem.para:
   The uWSGI server is now built with POSIX capabilities. As a consequence,
   root is no longer required in emperor mode and the service defaults to
   running as the unprivileged uwsgi user. Any additional
   capability can be added via the new option
   .
   The previous behaviour can be restored by setting:

= "root";
= "root";
=
 {
   uid = "uwsgi";
   gid = "uwsgi";
 };

Another incompatibility from the previous release is that vassals running under a
different user or group need to use immediate-{uid,gid}
instead of the usual uid,gid options.

The attribute mpi is now consistently used to provide a default, system-wide MPI implementation. The default implementation is openmpi, which has been used before by all derivations affects by this change. Note that all packages that have used mpi ? null in the input for optional MPI builds, have been changed to the boolean input paramater useMpi to enable building with MPI.
Building all packages with mpich instead of the default openmpi can now be achived like this:
self: super: { mpi = super.mpich; }
